name: Three Boons Yoga Charlottenburg‚Äìf.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Three Boons Yoga Charlottenburg‚Äìf.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10707', 'streetAddress': 'Kurf√ºrstendamm 177'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4999549', 'longitude': '13.3107685'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_de-live_venueHome_1024x576_Bild1_1616513376968717_admin_1714633525638751_admin.png?generation=1714633525817270&alt=media'}
description: Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.

name: Rocycle Berlin Mitte
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Rocycle Berlin Mitte', 'description': 'Rocycle is an effective, sweaty and fun workout that takes your mind off everything. We make our community fit and happy. Every day. Every ride. Our full-body 45- & 60-minute workouts on a bike are uplifting experiences. Set to candlelight and fueled by epic beats, our classes are made to give you that natural high. Ride the energy of the pack as you pedal out of the saddle for most of the class, training your core and raising your heart rate. You will train your upper body with hand weights and handlebar push-ups, then finish with head-to-toe stretching. Our workouts take your mind off everything, as you feel the endorphins rushing through your body. In an hour, you will walk out completely revitalized. Music is our mantra: Each class rocks a unique playlist handpicked by your instructor, from deep house and electronic to pop, hip-hop, and French house. Feel the chills from each song, let the beats lift you up and get carried away by the energy of the tracks. It can get a little emotional in here ‚Äì go with it! We like to call it the happiness effect. Get ready to pamper yourself in the changing rooms: After the class, drop your shoes and towel in the designated bins and drift towards the showers. We've made sure that you can really pamper yourself in our changing rooms. Luxurious fresh towels and Zenology‚Äôs line of organic care products await you ‚Äì including body wash, shampoo, conditioner and body lotion. The women‚Äôs changing room is also equipped with hair dryers and straighteners, so if you‚Äôre getting ready to take on the world that day, we‚Äôve got you covered.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10119', 'streetAddress': 'Linienstra√üe 41'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5283302', 'longitude': '13.409615'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_3000x1688_rocycle%20staged%20ride%20zuidas-78_1681377515363342_admin.jpg?generation=1681377515455893&alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Rocycle Berlin Kudamm', 'description': 'Rocycle is an effective, sweaty and fun workout that takes your mind off everything. Feel the chills from each song, let the beats lift you up and get carried away by the energy of the tracks. It can get a little emotional in here ‚Äì go with it! We like to call it the happiness effect. Get ready to pamper yourself in the changing rooms: After the class, drop your shoes and towel in the designated bins and drift towards the showers. We've made sure that you can really pamper yourself in our changing rooms. Luxurious fresh towels and Zenology‚Äôs line of organic care products await you ‚Äì including body wash, shampoo, conditioner and body lotion. The women‚Äôs changing room is also equipped with hair dryers and straighteners, so if you‚Äôre getting ready to take on the world that day, we‚Äôve got you covered.

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Three Boons Yoga Kreuzberg ‚Äì f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke', 'description': 'CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke bietet auf √ºber 700 m2 CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è, Hyrox, Gewichtheben, funktionelles Fitness- und Athletiktraining sowie Physiotherapie und Physiotraining vom Feinsten. Bitte beachte die folgenden Punkte bei der Anmeldung FAQ USC Member (for english version see below) 1. Wie erfolgt die Anmeldung f√ºr Kurse bei ICKE Die Anmeldung f√ºr die Kurse erfolgt √ºber unser Online Sales Portal: https://www.crossfiticke.com/usc/. Buche hier einen Drop-In um dich f√ºr einen Kurs anzumelden. Bei deiner Anmeldung musst du deinen vollen Namen sowie deine USC Membership Nummer angeben (USC 123456 Michael Mustermann) Vor Ort musst dann wie bei jedem USC Angebot den QR-Code scannen. 2.Welche Kurse kann ich mit meiner USC Membership besuchen? Alle Kurse die besuchen kannst, werden dir als Drop-In Optionen im Sales Portal von Icke angezeigt. 3.Wie oft kann ich mit meiner USC Membership bei CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke trainieren? Die L-Membership erlaubt es dir 4x im Monat ein CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Angebot zu nutzen. Mit der XL-Membership kannst du bis 8x im Monat CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è machen. 4.Ich habe mich f√ºr einen Kurs angemeldet, kann diesen Termin aber leider nicht wahrnehmen. Kein Problem. Ruf uns an oder schick uns eine Email und wir canceln deine Reservierung. Ber√ºcksichtige aber bitte, dass wir eine 24 Stundenfrist f√ºr Absagen haben. Solltest du deinen Termin innerhalb von 24 Stunden vor Kursbeginn absagen, gilt dies als Late-Cancelation und wir m√ºssen diesen trotzdem buchen. Nat√ºrlich buchen wir den Kurs auch, wenn du trotz Anmeldung nicht zum Training erschienen bist. 5.Wo finde ich CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke? Am einfachsten suchst du bei Google Maps nach CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke. Falls du vom S√ºdkreuz oder der Julius-Leber-Br√ºcke kommst haben wir aber auch eine Video-Wegbeschreibung f√ºr dich. Du findest diese auf unserer Kontaktseite https://www.crossfiticke.com/kontakt/ 6.Kann man bei euch duschen? Klar kannst du bei uns duschen. 7.Was brauche ich zum Training bei euch? Sportklamotten und Sportschuhe sind ein Muss! Wenn du mit Schuhen kommst die du auch drau√üen tr√§gst, kannst du nicht am Training teilnehmen. 8.Ihr seid geil! Wie werde ich bei euch Mitglied? Einfach unseren Webshop besuchen und Online einen Probemonat bei CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke abschlie√üen FAQ USC Member (for german version see above) 1. How do I sign up for classes at Icke? Please visit our online sales portal: https://www.crossfiticke.com/usc/ and make a reservation through the drop-in option. Please state your USC Membership number as well as your full name when making the reservation (USC 123456 John Doe) 2. Which classes can I attend as a USC member? All classes accessible for USC members are shown in the sales portal. 3.How often can I train at Icke using my USC membership? The L-membership will allow you to sign up for four classes per month at Icke. With the XL-membership you will be able to sign up for eight classes per month. 4.I signed up for a class but won‚Äôt be able to attend. No problemo. Send us an email or give us a ring and we‚Äôll cancel your drop-in. However, please be aware that we have a 24 hour cancelation policy, meaning that if you cancel inside a window of 24 h before the class is about to start this counts as a late-cancelation and we have to book your as if you had attended. The same obviously holds true if you made a reservation and never showed up. 5.Where do I find CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke? Easiest way is to look us up on Google Maps and follow the instructions. If you‚Äôre coming from either S-S√ºdkreuz or S-Julius-Leber-Br√ºcke you can find instructional videos from way back on our contact site: https://www.crossfiticke.com/kontakt/ 6.Do you have showers? Of course. They are awesome! 7.What do I need to train at Icke? You‚Äôll need sports clothes and indoor sports shoes. If you‚Äôre showing up in shoes that you used outdoor, you can‚Äôt train. 8.You guys rule! I want to become a CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke member! You‚Äôre cool too. Du findest diese auf unserer Kontaktseite https://www.crossfiticke.com/kontakt/ 6.Kann man bei euch duschen? Klar kannst du bei uns duschen. 7.Was brauche ich zum Training bei euch? Sportklamotten und Sportschuhe sind ein Muss! Wenn du mit Schuhen kommst die du auch drau√üen tr√§gst, kannst du nicht am Training teilnehmen. 8.Ihr seid geil! Wie werde ich bei euch Mitglied? Einfach unseren Webshop besuchen und Online einen Probemonat bei CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke abschlie√üen FAQ USC Member (for german version see above) 1. How do I sign up for classes at Icke? Please visit our online sales portal: https://www.crossfiticke.com/usc/ and make a reservation through the drop-in option. Please state your USC Membership number as well as your full name when making the reservation (USC 123456 John Doe) 2. Which classes can I attend as a USC member? All classes accessible for USC members are shown in the sales portal. 3.How often can I train at Icke using my USC membership? The L-membership will allow you to sign up for four classes per month at Icke. With the XL-membership you will be able to sign up for eight classes per month. 4.I signed up for a class but won‚Äôt be able to attend. No problemo. Send us an email or give us a ring and we‚Äôll cancel your drop-in. However, please be aware that we have a 24 hour cancelation policy, meaning that if you cancel inside a window of 24 h before the class is about to start this counts as a late-cancelation and we have to book your as if you had attended. The same obviously holds true if you made a reservation and never showed up. 5.Where do I find CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke? Easiest way is to look us up on Google Maps and follow the instructions. If you‚Äôre coming from either S-S√ºdkreuz or S-Julius-Leber-Br√ºcke you can find instructional videos from way back on our contact site: https://www.crossfiticke.com/kontakt/ 6.Do you have showers? Of course. They are awesome! 7.What do I need to train at Icke? You‚Äôll need sports clothes and indoor sports shoes. If you‚Äôre showing up in shoes that you used outdoor, you can‚Äôt train. 8.You guys rule! I want to become a CrossFit¬ÆÔ∏è Icke member! You‚Äôre cool too. Just visit our webshop and sign up for the intro-month.

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Three Boons Yoga Mitte ‚Äì f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.

name: Yoga Futura
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Futura', 'description': 'At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12059', 'streetAddress': 'Weigandufer 18'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4831013', 'longitude': '13.4471193'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2048x1152_dc2082d53fe4-ADDB06D3_6989_439A_B963_623DAE743A42_1644852605813520_admin.jpg?generation=1644852605910606&alt=media'}
description: At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Bodies By Tischa HIIT-Fit Studio - HIIT Training', 'description': 'My name is Tischa Thomas. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'SUPERNOVA Fitness', 'description': 'EMS - Trainiert, in nur 20 Minuten pro Woche! Je mehr Reize wir ihnen geben, desto schneller und besser verl√§uft ihr Wachstum. √úblicherweise √ºbernimmt diese Aufgabe unser zentrales Nervensystem, das die Reize an unsere Muskeln weiterleitet. Beim EMS-Training simulieren wir diese Reize mittels elektrischer Stromimpulse nach. Auf diese Weise werden unsere Muskeln in k√ºrzerer Zeit deutlich mehr Reizen ausgesetzt, was das EMS so enorm effektiv gegen√ºber herk√∂mmlichen Trainingsmethoden macht. Zudem spricht EMS die Tiefenmuskulatur an, die f√ºr deine Stabilit√§t und Beweglichkeit verantwortlich ist. Zeitraubendes Core- oder Functional-Training, Pilates oder Yoga k√∂nnen also durch gezieltes EMS-Training ersetzt oder zumindest erg√§nzt werden. Was ist das Beste an EMS? 20 Minuten pro Woche reichen aus f√ºr ein effektives Ganzk√∂rperworkout! Und keine Sorge: der Reizstrom ist weder gef√§hrlich, noch f√ºhlt er sich unangenehm an. Wir passen die Impulse ganz auf deine pers√∂nlichen W√ºnsche, Gef√ºhle und Trainingserfolge an. A shiatsu session takes place fully clothed, on a futon on the floor. Different techniques can be used and applied to the whole body, depending on the needs: mobilisation of joints, stretching of muscles, acupressure, relaxation. My name is Ma√Øt√©, I am a shiatsu wellness practitioner. I completed my training at the Shiatsu Schule Kreuzberg in Berlin with Harald Gierl in June 2022. name: Marcela Integral Relaxation and Prengnancy Massage
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Marcela Integral Relaxation and Prengnancy Massage', 'description': 'Integral Relaxing Massage, also for pregnants, near to Senefelderplatz - Prenzlauer Berg I am offering fascia touch, deep release massages, done with oil and OE essentials oils used in aromatherapies. You will have a calm and spacious room to relax and receive body work, while listening to calm music. For the massage you will have a warm mattress lying on the tatami, covered by warm blankets to remain the body warm while passively receiving the touch. As a Doula of birth, I can also work with the pregnant body as well, which helps balancing trigger points and well being during the pregnancy. The massage is perceived as wonderfully soothing and has a noticeable aftereffect. Among other things, the release touch can help to relieve stress, tensions, exhaustion, restlessness and many other disorders. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. name: the dopamine studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'the dopamine studio', 'description': 'Step into the Dopamine Studio, a uniquely crafted outdoor gym nestled in the heart of Berlin. No worries! Our courses cater to all levels, accommodating beginners and advanced individuals alike. Our dedicated coaches will ensure your well-being every step of the way. Please note that while we don't have showers, we provide an invigorating outdoor cold shower and outdoor toilet facilities for your convenience. Any questions? Reach out: simon@thedopaminestudio.com. No matter if you're a newcomer eager to explore calisthenics or an experienced practitioner aiming to elevate your skills. name: Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - indoor
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - indoor', 'description': 'I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10179', 'streetAddress': 'Inselstra√üe 9'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5122591', 'longitude': '13.4118726'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1125x633_9a5481caab7d-27F511FB_F648_415A_B725_BC8934B2D4A6_1657785499159017_admin.png?generation=1657785499222759&alt=media'}
description: I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe

name: Yoga Studio Santosha Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Studio Santosha Berlin', 'description': 'Our concept is ‚ÄúYoga as lifestyle‚Äù. Our studio name‚Äù Santosha‚Äù means contentment. A word from Yoga philosophy which means to be grateful for what we have and content with who we are and where are in life. We are living in competitive society and recently we are in covid-19 related confusion, we all have stress, most people are struggling how do we live with it. We are focus on breathing and stillness. We believe practicing yoga is one of the answers. Founder, Mika Ishige has been teaching yoga since 2007. From 2016, she has been teaching in Berlin. Completed 300h Yoga teacher training with Louisa Sear from Yoga arts (Yoga Alliance¬Æ 500h). Restorative Yoga and Pranayama teacher training with Cyndi Lee from OM Yoga. She learned Vinyasa yoga, Hatha yoga, Restorative yoga, Yin yoga, Therapeutic yoga, Ashtanga yoga, Pranayama (breathing technique) and Ayurveda. And we also have experienced and unique teacher in our team.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10115', 'streetAddress': 'Habersaathstra√üe 15'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5313891', 'longitude': '13.3756097'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_1_1635347193886449_admin.jpg?generation=1635347193989881&alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'L√ñWENHERZ WakeUp Pilates', 'description': '‚ÄûThe classes are demanding, full of energy and fun.‚Äú L√ñWENHERZ Power Pilates is based on the traditional Pilates exercises performed in a rather dynamic flow. name: Triathlon Crew Berlin HQ
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Triathlon Crew Berlin HQ', 'description': 'Willkommen bei der Triathloncrew Berlin. name: Ashtanga Yoga Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ashtanga Yoga Berlin', 'description': 'Ashtanga Yoga Berlin (since 2004) is the place for eager Yoga practitioners who seek guidance and precise support in the advanced and subtle Yoga practices. Ashtanga is a non-esoteric, straightforward practice method, deeply rooted in the mind-blowing yogic scriptures. Come if you are ready to practice Yoga every day so you can develop your personal advanced Yoga practice. Go beyond the mainstream! Call us: +493048496665. === WHAT IS ASHTANGA YOGA MYSORE STYLE? === Mysore Style is the classical Indian Yoga teaching method. Individual tuition in small groups (10 ‚Äì 20 practitioners) allows for cultivating an individual practice and ‚Äúinward-orientation‚Äù (pratyak-cetana) of your mind. The result is the exact opposite of the wide-spread (western) approach of ‚Äúteacher-imitation‚Äù, which directs your awareness outwards and puffs up the ego. True yogic experiences cannot arise if you look away from the self. Try the difference and you‚Äôll understand. === HOW CAN YOU LEARN MYSORE STYLE? === After a month of Mysore Style practice you will have escaped the boredom of flowery platitudes of copy-paste Yoga. But be warned: True Yoga needs method and dedication. Ashtanga is constructed to be challenging for your body, nervous system and ego structure. It‚Äôs all quite natural, just give us a call and we explain the details: +49.30.48496665. === YOU HAVE AN ASHTANGA PRACTICE? GO BEYOND! === If you know what you are doing you can simply join our Mysore classes any time. You will discover fascinating internal alignment tools which remove all major obstacles on your path with ease. Learn why mulabandha is not what you think and experience the true meaning of ‚Äúadvanced‚Äù in Yoga. === YOGA INJURIES? WHAT‚ÄôS THAT?!? === ‚ÄúAsana practice is (...) not which ruins someone‚Äôs health‚Äù - Adi Shankara, ca. 8th cent. CE. Both cause and solution for Shankara‚Äôs observation have not changed over the past 1200 years. Yoga injuries come from incorrect practice. Incorrect practice comes from incorrect teaching. Incorrect teaching is ignorantly serving the ego rather than the self. Injuries disappear when you stop re-injuring yourself. Your body heals within days when the cause of an injury is removed. That‚Äôs your inherent nature. It is that simple. We will help you. === THE MEANING OF YOGA === The process of Yoga is a fundamental transformation of how you perceive the world and your own self. The only valid map on that path are the ancient yogic scriptures such as Yoga Sutra, the Bhagavad Gita etc. This is our foundation, even if it looks like a physical practice. === BECOME PART OF OUR COMMUNITY === It is an important goal for us to build a community of practitioners from all yoga traditions. Let us create an island of mindful people. Let us chat, discuss questions and make new friends. Let us reflect and support each other. Let us care for all beings. name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - Studio2
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - Studio2', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: Yoga Futura Kreuzberg
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Futura Kreuzberg', 'description': 'At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10965', 'streetAddress': 'Kreuzbergstrasse 30'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4902944', 'longitude': '13.3777416'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_de-live_venueHome_1024x576_86ec5cb52ec8-AAFA09EB_A9B0_4F45_9BA9_99EB4F367D69_1644852610349229_admin_170003430549563_admin.jpg?generation=1700034305115972&alt=media'}

We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. name: Berlin Handstand School
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Handstand School', 'description': 'Luka is a mover that hasn't stopped moving since he left his IT chair some years ago. He is a bubble of ideas; about life, Acroyoga, and massage/bodywork. Very rarely a day passes without some kind of movement practice or community / teaching events. Luka has been teaching the past years around the world with a yearly 3 month stay in Japan and also South America and Europe. With the organisation Japanero.pro he organises events ranging from yoga, Acroyoga, partner acrobatics, handstands, massage and running - usually always in beautiful nature places around Europe. name: Ori Tahiti @ Atelier De La Danse
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ori Tahiti @ Atelier De La Danse', 'description': 'Polynesische T√§nze beinhalten viel mehr als nur sch√∂ne Bewegungen zu harmonischer oder temperamentvoller Musik. Te Ora bedeutet auf tahitianisch das Leben. Es geht um Geschichten des Lebens wie Liebe, besondere Begebenheiten oder die Natur. Man entwickelt hierbei auch einen entspannten Lebensstil im Geiste von Aloha, in Harmonie mit der Natur und den Menschen um uns herum bzw. mit uns selbst. Es geht um eine ganze Kultur und, indem wir tiefer in sie hinein tauchen durch den Tanz, verbinden wir uns tiefer mit ihr und bringen diesen Geist in unser gesamtes Leben ein. Andrea Claassen-Hansen ist ausgebildete B√ºhnent√§nzerin und hat 4 Lehrertrainings der Te Tuamarama International School of Tahitian Dance unter der Leitung von Joelle Berg (Conservatoire de Papeete) absolviert. Sie unterrichtet seit 2015 in dieser Lineage. Auch hat sie Kurse und Workshops im Rahmen der TU Hochschulsport Sektion Tanz abgehalten. Andrea unterrichtet in Berlin w√∂chentliche Kurse in Ori Tahiti Anf√§nger Online (Donnerstag) und Ori Tahiti Anf√§nger vor Ort im Studio (Sonntags) Polynesian dances contain much more than just beautiful movements to harmonious or spirited music. Te Ora means life in Tahitian. It is about stories of life like love, special events or nature. One also develops a relaxed lifestyle in the spirit of Aloha, in harmony with nature and the people around us or with ourselves. It is about a whole culture and, by diving deeper into it through dance, we connect more deeply with it and bring this spirit into our whole life. Andrea Claassen-Hansen is a trained stage dancer and has completed 4 teacher training courses at Te Tuamarama International School of Tahitian Dance under the direction of Joelle Berg (Conservatoire de Papeete). She has been teaching in this lineage since 2015. She has also held courses and workshops within the TU Hochschulsport Sektion Tanz. name: Merav Pilates - Heile Haus
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Merav Pilates - Heile Haus', 'description': 'Pilates with Merav Ben Dor. Coming from a background of dance and Yoga, I fell in love with Pilates as it helped me understand my body better, improved my dancing techniques and made me stronger and longer (and if not by actual centimeters, than at least by feeling). Not any less important- Pilates helped me regaining strength after the births of my three kids. Teaching Pilates for the last 7 years increased my appreciation both of the human body and its capabilities, and of the method itself. I have witnessed bodies change through and with the help of Pilates and believe that sometimes our body is wiser than our head, and we should just follow it to its full potential. The classes suit all levels and are putting an emphasis on the connection between breathing and moving, as well as researching the work of the body as a "whole made of separate parts". Hope to see you!', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Waldemarstr. 36'}, 'telephone': '+49 1573 0761074', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5035082', 'longitude': '13.4191845'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2448x1377_merav_1583424265762472_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Pilates with Merav Ben Dor. Coming from a background of dance and Yoga, I fell in love with Pilates as it helped me understand my body better, improved my dancing techniques and made me stronger and longer (and if not by actual centimeters, than at least by feeling). Not any less important- Pilates helped me regaining strength after the births of my three kids. Teaching Pilates for the last 7 years increased my appreciation both of the human body and its capabilities, and of the method itself. I have witnessed bodies change through and with the help of Pilates and believe that sometimes our body is wiser than our head, and we should just follow it to its full potential. The classes suit all levels and are putting an emphasis on the connection between breathing and moving, as well as researching the work of the body as a "whole made of separate parts". Hope to see you!

name: Ballett Centrum
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ballett Centrum', 'description': '√úber uns Seit bereits 30 Jahren begeistert das Ballett Centrum gro√üe und kleine Berliner f√ºr den Tanz. Mit dem st√§ndigen Bem√ºhen um die besten Lehrer in der Stadt machte es sich schnell einen Namen als eine f√ºhrende Ballettschule. Mit gro√üz√ºgigen R√§umen und einem breitgef√§cherten Kursangebot bieten wir allen Tanzliebhabern eine Vielzahl von M√∂glichkeiten, ihrer gro√üen Leidenschaft nachzugehen. Dabei verstehen wir uns als mehr als nur eine Ballettschule ‚Äì das Ballett Centrum ist ein generations√ºbergreifender Begegnungsort. Wir bieten eine B√ºhne f√ºr Berliner K√ºnstler und damit ein buntes Programm f√ºr unsere Besucher. Nach drei Jahrzehnten im Kurf√ºrstendamm Karree freuen wir uns, Sie an unserem neuen attraktiven Standort am Adenauerplatz begr√º√üen zu k√∂nnen! Unser Kursangebot Das ganzj√§hrige Angebot an Ballett, Modern Dance, Jazz-Tanz in verschiedensten Stilrichtungen (von Musical-Dance √ºber Modern-, Afro- und Hip-Hop-Jazz), Street Dance, Steptanz, Akrobatik, Yoga und Pilates ist kaum zu √ºberbieten. Das ganze Jahr hindurch wird unterrichtet, Ferien gibt es nur zu Weihnachten, Unsere Kurse sind nicht nur auf Profi-T√§nzer ausgerichtet - auch tanzbegeisterte Laien und Neu-Einsteiger sind willkommen! Bei uns finden Sie Tanzunterricht f√ºr jedes Niveau und jede Altersklasse, von Erwachsenen und Jugendlichen bis hin zu den Kleinsten. Ein p√§dagogisch hervorragend fundiertes Lehrer-Team k√ºmmert sich um unsere ‚ÄûT√§nzer von morgen‚Äú: Bereits Dreij√§hrige werden mit Bewegungsspielen an Musik, Rhythmus und Tanz herangef√ºhrt. Es gibt zahlreiche Ballettklassen wie auch Jazz Dance, Hip Hop, Street Dance und Steptanz f√ºr Kinder und Jugendliche, f√ºr jede Altersstufe und jedes Niveau. Da die Kinder-Statisterie der Deutschen Oper von unserer Lehrerin Susanne Lawrenz geleitet wird, haben unsere Sch√ºler/innen die M√∂glichkeit, auf der B√ºhne der Deutschen Oper aufzutreten. J√ºngst wurden sie sogar f√ºr eine Ballett-Einlage eingesetzt! Die Berliner Musicalschule Die besondere Qualit√§t der Berliner Musicalschule ist die intensive Betreuung und individuelle F√∂rderung jedes Auszubildenden. Sie ist nur durch intensive Arbeit in kleineren Semestergruppen gew√§hrleistet. Oberstes Ziel ist die Entwicklung der eigenen unverwechselbaren k√ºnstlerischen Pers√∂nlichkeit, um eine dauerhafte Konkurrenzf√§higkeit zu erreichen. Neugier und Kreativit√§t sind gefragt, um auf den eigenen k√ºnstlerischen Weg zu gelangen. Auch durch das reichhaltige Tanz-Angebot bietet die Berliner Musicalschule eine attraktive Alternative zu anderen Hochschulen und privaten Ausbildungsst√§tten. Durch die Anerkennung vom Senat als ‚ÄûPrivate Erg√§nzungsschule nach ¬ß 9a‚Äú k√∂nnen unsere Auszubildenden BAF√ñG beziehen. Um unsere Schule kennenzulernen, bieten wir die M√∂glichkeit einer Probewoche, in der man an allen Tanzklassen teilnehmen sowie bei Schauspiel-, Klavier- u. Gesangs-Unterricht zusehen kann. Ein Kultur-Treffpunkt Das Ballett Centrum ist √ºber die Funktion als Tanzschule hinaus seit jeher eine Begegnungsst√§tte und ein Schmelztiegel der K√ºnste - T√§nzer, Schauspieler, S√§nger, Musiker und bildende K√ºnstler kommen hier zusammen. So war die ‚ÄûTalent-Schmiede‚Äú gerade der richtige Drehort f√ºr die ZDF-Serie ‚ÄûSpiel des Lebens‚Äú √ºber eine Schauspielschule. Unsere Kurse Achtsamkeitsbasiertes Hatha-Yoga bildet die Grundlage f√ºr die Klassen. Egal ob schnell oder langsam, fliessend oder statisch, f√ºr Anf√§nger oder Ge√ºbte. Du kannst in allen Klassen in Deinem Rhythmus mitmachen. Wir achten darauf, dass Du Gelegenheit bekommst auf Dich selbst zu achten und haben einen Blick auf Dich, damit Du Dich sicher f√ºhlen und Deine Yogapraxis weiterentwickeln kannst. name: Ashtanga Yoga Zentral
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ashtanga Yoga Zentral', 'description': 'Ashtanga Yoga is an intensive Hatha Yoga practice with a focus on strength, stamina and flexibility. The traditional system is renowned for its Vinyasa method. This method of Yoga involves synchronising the breath with movement and positions, a process producing internal heat and a purifying sweat that detoxifies muscles and organs. Ashtanga Yoga is a moving meditation, resulting in improved circulation, a light and strong body, and a calm mind. Mysore-Style (named after the south-Indian city where it originated) is the traditional method in which Ashtanga Yoga is learned and practiced. Students receive individualised instruction within a group setting. A series of positions are taught in a specified order, progressing as the student is ready. With consistent, regular practice, the student can truly reap the benefits of Ashtanga yoga, bringing about the union of body and mind, one of the ultimate goals of yoga. Classes take place in the mornings and are open to all levels of practitioner, including those completely new to yoga.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10115', 'streetAddress': 'Grosse Hamburger Str. 19A'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5244355', 'longitude': '13.3988557'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1587x893_96345786363b-IMG_6146bb_1704871595538366_admin.jpg?generation=1704871595749486&alt=media'}
description: Ashtanga Yoga is an intensive Hatha Yoga practice with a focus on strength, stamina and flexibility. The traditional system is renowned for its Vinyasa method. This method of Yoga involves synchronising the breath with movement and positions, a process producing internal heat and a purifying sweat that detoxifies muscles and organs. Ashtanga Yoga is a moving meditation, resulting in improved circulation, a light and strong body, and a calm mind. Mysore-Style (named after the south-Indian city where it originated) is the traditional method in which Ashtanga Yoga is learned and practiced. Students receive individualised instruction within a group setting. A series of positions are taught in a specified order, progressing as the student is ready. With consistent, regular practice, the student can truly reap the benefits of Ashtanga yoga, bringing about the union of body and mind, one of the ultimate goals of yoga. Classes take place in the mornings and are open to all levels of practitioner, including those completely new to yoga.

name: Soul And Style
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Soul And Style', 'description': 'Hello Yogis and Yoginis we are Soul And Style! Soul stands for Yoga and Style for Vintage. As the name already says, we are not only a Yoga Studio, but as well a Vintage Store. To enter our Yoga facilities, one has to pass the store and even change in the store‚Äôs changing rooms. We renovated the studio ourselves, built in a wooden floor and cleared the beautiful brick walls, to make everyone feel as comfortable as possible. We love it colorful. Just like the store the studio is full of colors, bright and the light is reflected in the mirrors. We really want to get to know everyone around and in the Kiez. name: Heart Space
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Heart Space', 'description': 'Heart Space is a place of warmth, positivity and acceptance in which one trusts the wisdom of the body, rather than the intelligence of the mind. Here, we embrace it all: the day and night, darkness and light, rest and activity - we do not see yin and yang as opponents but rather as pairs that complement and support each other. We encourage you to listen to your own body, mind and soul, and choose the class that balances you in this moment of life: is it an energizing vinyasa flow, a relaxing yin practice, an activating breathwork session, a soulful sound bath, or a mindful meditation? We share from the heart with the people we love, and aim to make our classes available for everyone: from yoga newbies to enlightened yogis; for all bodies, genders and backgrounds. To extend our heart collective 5% of our profit goes to Yoga f√ºr alle e.V. for making yoga available to everyone (https://www.yogahilft.com/mission/) Please bring your own mat, if you have one, and arrive 10-15 min before the class to allow everyone to arrive and settle. You find us in Friedrichshain, close to Ostkreuz: Boxhagener Str. 77, 3. OG. Also let us know if you have any suggestions or recommendations :-) We look forward to welcoming you! x Laura & Linda', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10245', 'streetAddress': 'Boxhagener Str. 77'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5077466', 'longitude': '13.4689323'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1674x942_fbf715bca77c-Heart_Space_Yoga_Berlin_3_1698135781248212_admin.jpg?generation=1698135781323327&alt=media'}

name: kizomba mit kizombaberlin.de - Lichtenberg
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'kizomba mit kizombaberlin.de - Lichtenberg', 'description': 'I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10367', 'streetAddress': 'Rudolf Reusch Stra√üe 50'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5183968', 'longitude': '13.4829105'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1036x583_IMG_2867_1665998959321774_admin.jpg?generation=1665998959389957&alt=media'}
description: I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe

name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - ADA studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - ADA studio', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '13357', 'streetAddress': 'Badstr. 41a'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5533873', 'longitude': '13.3772948'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1879x1057_2a0811651c69-sundaysolos_photo_Andi_Weiland_112__2__16911631329392_admin.jpg?generation=1691163132078457&alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: Hoop Plus Fit 2
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Hoop Plus Fit 2', 'description': 'Hula hooping is an excellent way to get fit, stay strong and an excellent party trick to pull in front of your friends! We work mainly with waist hooping in order to build the strength and control needed to dance freely with the hoop around the waist and improve flow. In the tricks classes we train new skills and work on getting a better technique at every stage. I break down tricks into small achievable steps and which we use as building blocks for getting the trick. I also teach the tricks in small sequences, so we learn how to flow in and out of them from the beginning. As well as how to time your movement to the music. Aside from the Class I also run the The Hoop Plus Jam. This is is an open training session with a live DJ every week.There is a great sound system there, so you can feel the music and flow. Get Fit! name: Ana Kavalis - Somatische Akademie Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ana Kavalis - Somatische Akademie Berlin', 'description': 'The resonant body. Body-voice work training and movement research This training is based on improvisation, physical theater training, butoh dance practices, and somatic bodywork. Through a guided, animated warm-up, individual and partner improvisations, the aim of this training is to let our body grow towards unknown physical/ mind/ spirit states. It proposes both physical and vocal work focused on the connection between movement and breathing, the work with the energy, and our time-space awareness. Bringing more consciousness to our body-mind allows us to get out of our daily habits and facilitate access to our creativity in a more fluid and generous way. In addition, we will explore the relationship between movement and imagery. The imagery is understood as inner space that can emerge on the surface as a physical event that transforms us today and now. Open to performers, dancers, actors, and anyone interested in creative body research.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Paul-Linker-Ufer 30'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.495361', 'longitude': '13.4260105'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_7534x4238_aa4cb9e5a39e-2024.01.29_Resonantboday_logo_FINAL_Mesa_de_trabajo_1_copia_11_1713169945662278_admin.png?generation=1713169945758515&alt=media'}
description: The resonant body. Body-voice work training and movement research This training is based on improvisation, physical theater training, butoh dance practices, and somatic bodywork. Through a guided, animated warm-up, individual and partner improvisations, the aim of this training is to let our body grow towards unknown physical/ mind/ spirit states. It proposes both physical and vocal work focused on the connection between movement and breathing, the work with the energy, and our time-space awareness. Bringing more consciousness to our body-mind allows us to get out of our daily habits and facilitate access to our creativity in a more fluid and generous way. In addition, we will explore the relationship between movement and imagery. The imagery is understood as inner space that can emerge on the surface as a physical event that transforms us today and now. Open to performers, dancers, actors, and anyone interested in creative body research.

The Mindful approach to breath and body in our practices impacts clarity of mind and activates our deep core line. As human beings we are gifted with resilience and Yoga can help us explore this powerful tool. The classes are focused on the principle of Mindfulness with attention towards classical asanas and contemporary biomechanics. The classes offered are a balance of grounding/core/balance/inversions exercises and guided meditation, effort and ease, curated soundtrack and silence. Mixed level from beginners to advanced. Classes are in english, italian and spanish are also available.

ISHTA practice adapts to each yogi‚Äôs own needs and supports them to find the practice that suits them, with humor and ease. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'The Way Back Home - Osmos Studio', 'description': 'Yoga for The Way Back Home to ourSelves: A yoga and meditation practice rooted in nondual tantra philosophy, for revealing and (re)connecting to your true, essential nature, and for exploring ways of honouring your essence and its authentic expression. name: Pilates & Prenatal Pilates
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Pilates & Prenatal Pilates ', 'description': 'Luka is a mover that hasn't stopped moving since he left his IT chair some years ago. He is a bubble of ideas; about life, Acroyoga, and massage/bodywork. Very rarely a day passes without some kind of movement practice or community / teaching events. name: Anne Pawlak
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Anne Pawlak', 'description': 'Curious about building real strength, stamina and coordination? Trying a holistic way of moving and breathing to improve posture and body feeling? Then you are in the right place. Anne offers exactly that in her fun and effective Warm Body - Good Vibes classes and Breath Club sessions. Anne‚Äôs practise combines elements of HIIT, Animal Moves, Dance and Yoga. The Foundation for confident movement and wellbeing is effective breathing. "Most of our daily activities take us out of our body and disrupt the body and mind connection. Breathwork allows us to return to our neutral self where we can become creative, explosive, expressive and dynamic in our body and mind. And most of all joyful and content with ourselves." Feel free to bring your own mat and towel. To make the most of your training make sure to hydrate properly about an hour before the training. Anne discovered the power of breath after overtraining her body for years, which caused hormonal imbalances and over exhaustion. Through dedicated breath and meditation practise in Japan as well as syncing her workout with her hormonal cycle, she was able to return back to a grounded balance. "Many of my clients are high performers at work and at home with little time on their hands. High workloads, higher responsibilities and even higher stress levels. This means they are often sleep poorly, feel too exhausted, and have a bad conscience when they don't give it their all in workouts. I make sure to design a balanced practise that works for them so they can feel good in their body ."', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '', 'streetAddress': 'Volkspark Friedrichshain'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5280353', 'longitude': '13.4363934'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_e4d0b13f17a7-UrbanSports2_1624976944712241_admin.jpg?alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'B-side Yoga @ Vea Studio', 'description': 'B-side Yoga combines playful and functional movement with mindfulness. name: Berimbarte Capoeira @Caminada
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berimbarte Capoeira @Caminada', 'description': 'Capoeira is an Afro-Brazilian martial art. It combines various self defense and fighting techniques with rhythm, dance and acrobatics. The traditional music is a big part of the Capoeira culture and is also practiced and performed by the participants. The Capoeira group BerimbArte e.V. was founded in 2006 in Berlin. The name means ‚ÄúArt of the Berimbau‚Äù, the main instrument and a symbol of Capoeira. The group arranges a various amount of workshops, competitions and excursions every year. Privately the participants often meet up for additional trainings in the park, barbecue or just for beer and wine. The founder and main trainer of the group is Mestre Canguru (Lourival Pereira dos Santos). He started training Capoeira in 1989 in Brazil with the age of 12. In 1998 he moved to Berlin to bring the Capoeira culture to Europe. Today he has more than 25 years experience as a trainer and additional experience in BJJ and Muay Boran. No matter if newbie or veteran, everyone is welcome! Spoken languages in our group so far are German, English, Portuguese, French, Spanish and Italian.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10967', 'streetAddress': 'B√∂ckhstra√üe 21'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4931623', 'longitude': '13.4198767'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1600x900_Profilbild_16HX5.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Capoeira is an Afro-Brazilian martial art. It combines various self defense and fighting techniques with rhythm, dance and acrobatics. The traditional music is a big part of the Capoeira culture and is also practiced and performed by the participants. The Capoeira group BerimbArte e.V. was founded in 2006 in Berlin. The name means ‚ÄúArt of the Berimbau‚Äù, the main instrument and a symbol of Capoeira. The group arranges a various amount of workshops, competitions and excursions every year. Privately the participants often meet up for additional trainings in the park, barbecue or just for beer and wine. The founder and main trainer of the group is Mestre Canguru (Lourival Pereira dos Santos). He started training Capoeira in 1989 in Brazil with the age of 12. In 1998 he moved to Berlin to bring the Capoeira culture to Europe. Today he has more than 25 years experience as a trainer and additional experience in BJJ and Muay Boran. No matter if newbie or veteran, everyone is welcome! Spoken languages in our group so far are German, English, Portuguese, French, Spanish and Italian.

name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - Circus SCHATZINSEL
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - Circus SCHATZINSEL', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10997', 'streetAddress': 'May-Ayim-Ufer 4'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5022561', 'longitude': '13.4419975'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576__MG_3874%20edited_1595576967748982_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: Bihter Yoga
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Bihter Yoga', 'description': 'Bihter Yoga Yoga is a life altering experience! Hello, My name is Bihter. I believe that the discovery of the body is a life long experiment. Exchanging knowledge for me is an experience of expansion, enables us to learn from each other, grow together and support each other in this path. Besides my Hatha Yoga training within the Advaita School and mindfulness; my interest in Sufism and Buddhism as life philosophies and my interest in axis syllabus and bio-mechanics as tool kits to understand the body, shape my yoga teaching. In a 75 minutes of a yoga class I offer meditation, mindfulness, breathing techniques and classic yoga poses with a contemporary understanding enriched with bio-mechanics. Besides that I offer 60 minutes beginners class which we look into basics of yoga. I do classes with maximum 7 participants, and might be that you can‚Äôt get in if you don‚Äôt let me know you‚Äôre coming in advance. Please ring Raum5 and arrive latest 5 minutes before the class starts.
