name: Common Humanity - Evolve Yoga Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Common Humanity - Evolve Yoga Berlin', 'description': 'Common Humanity, Berlin's English-speaking mindfulness center, was created first and foremost to bring people together. Its mission is to create a warm and inviting space that allows members to build community, live a healthier lifestyle and tap into their own wisdom regardless of religion, background or political affiliation. As the name suggests, we have much more in common than we realize. We have much to learn from each other and we are more effective together. Through mindfulness, meditation and community we can better realize our personal potential and find greater stability in an increasingly chaotic world. Mindfulness Meditation can: * reduce stress and tension * boost your immune system * give you a greater understanding of yourself and others * prevent against "burnout" * increase your creativity * and much more Are you unfamiliar with mindfulness or mindful meditation? If so, we invite you to come and sit with us for an hour. You don't need any experience; however, all levels are welcome. Our hour-long meditations include 2-3 mindful meditations centered around a theme, followed by a short group discussion. Meditations will be in English, but please do not be intimidated. There is a great deal of silence in meditation, and you will not be required to write a master's thesis (we promise). If you have never had the opportunity to meditate in a group setting, you will find it to be a different (and potentially more enriching) experience from sitting alone. Kim Douglass is the founder and facilitator of the hour-long meditation sessions. She is an American Expat that has lived in Germany since 2006. She worked for many years in the corporate world, most recently as the Marketing Communications Manager for a tech company in Berlin. After her daughter was born in 2013, she had a serious bout with post-partum depression (PPD), which caused her to look for a solution that did not involve medication. Everything she read pointed to meditation. After much research, reading, meditating and yoga practice, she left her career to pursue a future teaching mindfulness to others because her life was changed so dramatically. Kim completed her Mindfulness, Meditation, and MBSR teacher training at Mindful Academy in Spain in 2017 and is enthusiastic about teaching people a more joyful and hopeful way to live their lives with a dash of mindfulness and a lot more kindness. You can find out more about Common Humanity on their website: www.commonhumanityberlin.com', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12159', 'streetAddress': 'Rheinstra√üe 67'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.471812', 'longitude': '13.335946'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_MeditationEvolve_1551431177266126_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Common Humanity, Berlin's English-speaking mindfulness center, was created first and foremost to bring people together. Its mission is to create a warm and inviting space that allows members to build community, live a healthier lifestyle and tap into their own wisdom regardless of religion, background or political affiliation. As the name suggests, we have much more in common than we realize. We have much to learn from each other and we are more effective together. Through mindfulness, meditation and community we can better realize our personal potential and find greater stability in an increasingly chaotic world. Mindfulness Meditation can: * reduce stress and tension * boost your immune system * give you a greater understanding of yourself and others * prevent against "burnout" * increase your creativity * and much more Are you unfamiliar with mindfulness or mindful meditation? If so, we invite you to come and sit with us for an hour. You don't need any experience; however, all levels are welcome. Our hour-long meditations include 2-3 mindful meditations centered around a theme, followed by a short group discussion. Meditations will be in English, but please do not be intimidated. There is a great deal of silence in meditation, and you will not be required to write a master's thesis (we promise). If you have never had the opportunity to meditate in a group setting, you will find it to be a different (and potentially more enriching) experience from sitting alone. Kim Douglass is the founder and facilitator of the hour-long meditation sessions. She is an American Expat that has lived in Germany since 2006. She worked for many years in the corporate world, most recently as the Marketing Communications Manager for a tech company in Berlin. After her daughter was born in 2013, she had a serious bout with post-partum depression (PPD), which caused her to look for a solution that did not involve medication. Everything she read pointed to meditation. After much research, reading, meditating and yoga practice, she left her career to pursue a future teaching mindfulness to others because her life was changed so dramatically. Kim completed her Mindfulness, Meditation, and MBSR teacher training at Mindful Academy in Spain in 2017 and is enthusiastic about teaching people a more joyful and hopeful way to live their lives with a dash of mindfulness and a lot more kindness. You can find out more about Common Humanity on their website: www.commonhumanityberlin.com

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'E & M Bachata - Nou Tango', 'description': 'Martyna, with 7 years of background in Bachata and Salsa, has been teaching internationally in the UK, Lithuania, and finally in Berlin. name: Groove - Tricks & Flow - Hula hoop class
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Groove - Tricks & Flow - Hula hoop class', 'description': 'Groove ist haupts√§chlich eine Musikschule f√ºr Percussion, an der auch Tanzkurse unterrichtet werden. Ist ein sehr herzlicher und einladender Ort im Herzen von Neuk√∂lln. Es gibt dort ein Caf√©, das viele leckere Snacks und Speisen aus Brasilien sowie Erfrischungen anbietet. name: Haus Lebenskunst
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Haus Lebenskunst', 'description': 'Osho Dynamische Meditation - Unser Energie-Booster zum Loslassen von Blockaden und zur R√ºckverbindung mit unserer Essenz! Ein 5 Phasen-Prozess, der dich durch Aufladung, Katharsis, Erdung und Meditation bis hin zu Freude und Feiern f√ºhrt. Phase (10 Min): Wildes, unregelm√§√üiges Atmen Lass deinem Atem freien Lauf und sei dabei so wild und unregelm√§√üig wie m√∂glich. Konzentriere dich dabei ausschlie√ülich auf das Ausatmen, denn das Einatmen wird von deinem K√∂rper von alleine gesteuert. Atme so schnell und kraftvoll, wie du nur kannst ‚Äì und dann noch ein bisschen energischer. Stelle dir vor, du verwandelst dich in puren Atem. Nutze die nat√ºrlichen Bewegungen deines K√∂rpers, um noch mehr Energie zu sp√ºren. Du wirst f√ºhlen, wie diese Energie zunimmt, aber lass sie noch nicht v√∂llig in der ersten Phase entweichen. Sie ist wie ein wildes Pferd, das du behutsam z√§hmen und lenken kannst. Phase (10 Min): Sich ausdr√ºcken Jetzt ist es an der Zeit, vollkommen auszubrechen! Lass alles los, was in dir brodelt und nach Freiheit schreit. Schreie, br√ºlle, weine, h√ºpfe, sch√ºttele dich, tanze, singe, lache und tobe herum. Keine Zur√ºckhaltung, kein Halten von Emotionen! Es ist v√∂llig in Ordnung, am Anfang ein bisschen zu √ºbertreiben, um in den Fluss zu kommen. Lass deinen Verstand nicht dazwischenfunken. Sei voll und ganz im Moment, lass dein Herz die F√ºhrung √ºbernehmen. Sei absolut authentisch und hingebungsvoll dabei. Das ist deine Zeit, deine Emotionen und deine Energie zu entfesseln. Erlaube dir selbst, frei zu sein und in dieser Phase alles auszuleben, was in dir steckt. Phase (10 Min): Mit erhobenen Armen springen Jetzt wird es noch intensiver! Stehe auf und hebe deine Arme in die H√∂he. Beginne, auf und ab zu springen, und rufe dabei das Mantra "Huh! Huh! Huh!" aus deinem Bauch heraus, so tief und kraftvoll wie du nur kannst. Lasse die Vibrationen dieses Mantras durch deinen K√∂rper pulsieren. Deine Arme sollen den Himmel ber√ºhren, und deine Stimme soll die Energie nach au√üen tragen. Du bist in einem Moment v√∂lliger Ekstase und Befreiung. Kein Grund zur Zur√ºckhaltung ‚Äì lasse dich vollst√§ndig von diesem Prozess erfassen und genie√üe die Freiheit, die er dir schenkt. Deine Energie ist grenzenlos, also lass sie str√∂men! Phase (15 Min): Still sein, nichts tun Stopp! Halte abrupt inne und bleibe genau in der Position, in der du gerade bist. Versuche nicht, es dir bequem zu machen, und vermeide jede Bewegung. Jede noch so kleine Bewegung oder Ablenkung k√∂nnte die aufgebaute Energie zerstreuen, und all deine Bem√ºhungen w√§ren umsonst. Nun geht es darum, alles, was in dir geschieht, aufmerksam zu beobachten. Deine Empfindungen, Emotionen, Gedanken - lass sie einfach kommen und gehen, ohne in sie zu vertiefen oder Widerstand zu leisten. Du bist ein stiller Beobachter deines eigenen Inneren. Diese Phase erlaubt dir, in eine tiefere Ebene deines Bewusstseins einzutauchen und die Effekte der vorherigen Phasen zu verarbeiten. name: Hyon Haeng Martial Arts
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Hyon Haeng Martial Arts', 'description': 'Sweat more in training, bleed less in battle. Following this creed this course aims to invigorate your body and mind, enable you to defend yourself and get you ready for combat. Chinese Martial Arts combines hundreds of disciplines for self defence and holistic fitness, which were developed and improved over centuries in the Middle Kingdom. They connect techniques for physical, mental and spiritual balance, which makes them useful for everybody at any stage of life. ' Aldo started his trainings at the age of 16 with Wushu and Sanda in Mexico City. After several years of intensive training he became a diciple of the Shaolin monk Shi Yan Bin to learn the wisdom and techniques of Shaolin Kung Fu. In 2004 he finally was able to go to China to receive a comprehensive training in a multitude of Chinese Martial Arts disciplines. Now he is bringing that wisdom to Berlin to share it with you. In this course the techniques of Sanda, Kickboxing, Shaolin kung fu, Tai chi and Choy lei fut are combined to not only help you reach your training goals, but also to strengthen your confidence and your resiliency. Curious? name: Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - outdoor
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - outdoor', 'description': 'I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10437', 'streetAddress': 'Mauerpark'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.54553', 'longitude': '13.404'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1125x633_9a5481caab7d-27F511FB_F648_415A_B725_BC8934B2D4A6_1657788682963547_admin.png?generation=1657788683022589&alt=media'}
description: I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe

name: MOVEMENT DANCE
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'MOVEMENT DANCE', 'description': 'The work integrates anatomy elements with the process of moving and dancing, for the pleasure of the body considered as our habit and medium of adaptness. An investigation on movement anchored to contemporary dance and based on perceptions and body awareness, mainly for the joy of experiencing movements in space, testing one's potential and individual expression. The class results in a dynamic mix between listening, energic exercises and rhythmical steps regarding coordination. We line the body and dive deep into its physicality by introducing a specific task in the form of somatic or technical matter. We gradually enable dividual tools and include severals variables of contemporary dance: weight, space, time, dynamics. Next we bring into play variations of speed and energy, spatial relations and projections through different lengths of sequences and guided improvisation. The aim is to reach a dynamic state that leads body and mind into a fluent dance. The personal presence, with its own specific language, is engaged and liberated to express itself, to co-exist and to enjoy the dance. Stefania works as dancer, maker and dance-teacher in Berlin where she moved in 2013. She got her degree in Dance & Pedagogy in Milan by C.I.M.D. in 2018, followed by studies with several choreographers and in different dance techniques included Instant Composition. She have been making dance and pieces as solos, in collectives and in big or small companies. She is co-founder of the ensemble One:Third (preis 100¬∞Berlin Festival 2015) and others dance collective. She is active on the Berlin scene as improviser, constantly experiencing new and multidisciplinary collaborations in live-performances. She teachs to adults and (even very young) children As teacher, her practice tracks integrations of physical skills and techniques in contemporary dance with Instant Composition principles, assuming first the joy in moving and dancing.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10997', 'streetAddress': 'Mariannenplatz 2'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5038945', 'longitude': '13.4240746'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_3634x2044_fullsizeoutput_20f9_1547473543400611_admin.jpeg?alt=media'}

The class results in a dynamic mix between listening, energic exercises and rhythmical steps regarding coordination. We line the body and dive deep into its physicality by introducing a specific task in the form of somatic or technical matter. We gradually enable dividual tools and include severals variables of contemporary dance: weight, space, time, dynamics. Next we bring into play variations of speed and energy, spatial relations and projections through different lengths of sequences and guided improvisation. The aim is to reach a dynamic state that leads body and mind into a fluent dance. name: Massage With Simon
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Massage With Simon', 'description': 'The two types of massage I do are sports/deep tissue and relaxation/classical. I have been working as a massage therapist since 2014, in gyms, spas and as a freelancer. I studied Remedial Massage and Relaxation Massage in Australia. Before each session, we do a quick check in, to see what areas you would like to have worked on, and what level of physical intensity you would like for today. During the session, I will check in to see that the pressure is the right amount for you. You may talk as little or as much as you like, for me I don‚Äôt mind what our conversation level is. I will mirror you, as this helps to create an experience that matches your needs. How does massage work? The most likely specific mechanism of how massage works is through touch, with strength of intensity being an individual preference. name: Move from within - @Innenraum
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Move from within - @Innenraum', 'description': 'About me I‚Äôm Eszter and I‚Äôm a holistic dance-movement facilitator and yoga teacher based in Berlin. Movement and being in contact with my body has always been a crucial part of my life but at some point it became fully clear that this is what I‚Äôd like to dedicate my professional life to ‚Äî I‚Äôm absolutely fascinated by the wisdom of the body and the wealth of knowledge and experiences we can find through (re-)connecting to it. My movement experience is varied and interdisciplinary: from a decade of yoga practice to various improvisational/contemporary dance movement modalities as well as many somatic practices are all informing my work and my approach to the body in movement. My main movement language is improvisation based on play, sensing and listening. Whether yoga or dance/movement, what I offer is influenced by an ongoing research into my own body, mind and spirit and therefore has a constantly evolving form. Focusing on cultivating awareness, letting whatever is present to come to the surface. ‚ÄúMovement is not something we do nearly so much as what we are, and harbinger to what we can become.‚Äù ‚Äî Sonja Fraleigh About the Movement Journey The Movement Journey is an open dance/movement exploration class with the aim of finding ease in movement, of finding different ways to move and of reestablishing contact with the body, the self and others. What will happen? We will work through various exercises inspired by contemporary improvisation, Gaga‚Äôs rich movement language, partner scores from contact improvisation as well as somatic approaches like Body-Mind Centering or Feldenkrais. All of this combined into a continuous movement journey that has a different focus each time. Sometimes it‚Äôs going to be soft and sensitive, other times explosive and fast. We will find new and exciting ways to move our bodies, we will practise moving with ease, stability, flexibility and agility. It‚Äôs an invitation to leave our rational, thinking minds at the door to tap into the world of sensing, feeling and listening ‚Äì to connect to ourselves and to others more and to give ourselves an opportunity to see what‚Äôs present for us at the moment and what wants to come up. Who are these classes for? - Everyone that feels life can be livelier, more full and whole - Everyone who would like to feel into their bodies and thus connect to themselves - Everyone that wishes to discover new and exciting ways to move, finding their own movement language - For everyone‚Ä¶ :) When and where? Every Tuesday: 7pm at _innenraum (Landsberger Allee 61, 10249 Berlin) Every Wednesday: 6pm at b23.studio (Greifswalder str. 23, 10405 Berlin) Stay updated via instagram: @eszterkaloz or through my telegram channel: telegram.me/movementjourney', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10405', 'streetAddress': 'Landsberger Allee 61'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.525625', 'longitude': '13.4434188'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2000x1125_8774458af0ad-Copy_of_flyer_design_1_1697444330529905_admin.png?generation=1697444330602090&alt=media'}

name: Movement Meditation with Tamara @Optionsraum
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Movement Meditation with Tamara @Optionsraum', 'description': 'Here in Optionsraum, a very spacious and bright studio located right on the SPRE River you can experience yourself in Open Floor Movement Meditation. OPEN FLOOR is a somatic and movement meditation practice ‚Äì physical, sensual, pleasurable and rich in knowledge. It brings self-awareness, mindfulness, and purpose to life. It helps us to reconnect with the wisdom of our body and heart. It deepens the connection to yourself, your relationships and the world around you. Open Floor integrates therapeutic, creative and spiritual approaches with free movement. For who those classes are designed: for those who are thirsty to connect with oneself or others, who want to feel accepted, understood and inspired. And for those of you who want to rebuild yourself, relax, satisfy the need for flow and togetherness, to feel one‚Äôs body better and get free from the stories of your mind. What can you expect: lightness, freedom, movement, sense of refreshment. You will probably meet yourself from a new perspective. Maybe you will appreciate something new in yourself. You may experience the rebuilding power of empathy for yourself and others around you, a surge of energy and an increased sense of creativity. What will you receive: You will relax and take home a sense of well-being ‚Äì a better foundation, new ideas, a fresh look at yourself. Each class will give you a new resource to support you in your next week and every daily life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10179', 'streetAddress': 'Wilhelmine-Gemberg-Weg 12'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5108369', 'longitude': '13.4249583'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2048x1152_adu7ps8niw7ujohbdn6y_1687424664919161.png?generation=1687424665145278&alt=media'}

name: Nada-space Viktoria Park
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Nada-space Viktoria Park', 'description': 'Summer gifts us the precious time to share in nature. Grundelemente aus der Technik des ¬´ Mime Corporel Dramatique ¬ª von Etienne Decroux, mit vielen Abweichungen in die Tradition der Commedia dell‚ÄôArte, bis in die Innovation des zeitgen√∂ssischen ¬´ Physical Theatre. ¬ª PHYSICAL DRAMA erarbeitet alle Facetten des Bewegungs- und Wortlosen Theaters: vom Drama bis zum Grotesken, Mime, Clown, Masque und auch Objektmanipulation. name: Pilates Let's Go Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Pilates Let's Go Berlin', 'description': 'The classes of Pilates Let's Go Berlin are taught in German and French! What is Pilates ? It's a system of physical conditioning involving low-impact exercises and stretches designed to strengthen muscles of the torso , the Spine, abs, and the other muscles. It's a good way to maintain a good physical condition with time¬ª My classes : My classes are for people who want to discover pilates, and who do sport or for beginners too (people who don't have the time to practice any sport beside their work). I teach in french and german. I teach in small groups, the room where I teach is small, and I can accept maximum 7 people per class. So it's always better to reserve in advance your spot. I like the proximity with my students and find important to pay attention to each person during my class, I prefer quality over quantity. My class lasts one hour, composed with a warm up, differents series of exercices, and stronger exercices at the end, I always finish the class with a relax time, which allows people who are stressed before the class, to feel more centered and relaxed at the end. It can also be for people who have back pain, in this case I ask the person to talk before with his doctor or physiotherapist, if she can paractice pilates. People who come to my classes are most women, but men are also welcome !! Pilates is for everybody of all ages (from Teenagers to old people). A regular practice of Pilates allows to work at the same time the center of Body, concentration, strength, flexibility, to work the breath but also the resistance, and have a better control of the body. ACHTUNG: Dieser Kurs ist auf 7 Teilnehmer begrenzt. Bitte buche deinen Termin 24 Stunden vorher. ATTENTION: This class is for 7 students only. Please book your mat 24 hours in advance.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10783', 'streetAddress': 'Kulmer Strasse 18'}, 'telephone': '+49 1511 2764976', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4923956', 'longitude': '13.3647411'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1460x821_43025677_2245249332355262_3764502920427470848_n_1554804568663912_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: The classes of Pilates Let's Go Berlin are taught in German and French! What is Pilates ? It's a system of physical conditioning involving low-impact exercises and stretches designed to strengthen muscles of the torso , the Spine, abs, and the other muscles. It's a good way to maintain a good physical condition with time¬ª My classes : My classes are for people who want to discover pilates, and who do sport or for beginners too (people who don't have the time to practice any sport beside their work). I teach in french and german. I teach in small groups, the room where I teach is small, and I can accept maximum 7 people per class. So it's always better to reserve in advance your spot. I like the proximity with my students and find important to pay attention to each person during my class, I prefer quality over quantity. My class lasts one hour, composed with a warm up, differents series of exercices, and stronger exercices at the end, I always finish the class with a relax time, which allows people who are stressed before the class, to feel more centered and relaxed at the end. It can also be for people who have back pain, in this case I ask the person to talk before with his doctor or physiotherapist, if she can paractice pilates. People who come to my classes are most women, but men are also welcome !! Pilates is for everybody of all ages (from Teenagers to old people). name: S√¨Yoga
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'S√¨Yoga', 'description': 'S√¨Yoga is an Ashtanga Vinyasa Teaching Project, kicked off in March 2020 online during the Covid19 pandemic. Especially in this particular time, I believe yoga offers us a solution, an escape, a way to unwind. We use the asanas (yoga postures) to get into the body and reconnect with the universal consciousness. What my students enjoy, it's my positive energy, my motivation and my ability to explain the postures at different levels. A bit about my self: Italian by birth, Berliner by choice and multilingual as result, I decided to take the step and turn my passion for yoga into a career. In September 2019 I travelled to India to attend the 200-hour Ashtanga Yoga Teaching Training in Mysore. Upon completion, I continued to follow my yoga practice wherever I was, unrolling the yoga mat on Nepalese hills, on the rooftops of Indian and Burmese hostels, or on white beaches of the Philippines or Cambodia. Yoga made me feel free and helped me connect with other open-minded people. That's how I became a teacher and I'm now grateful to share and teach with passion and commitment this life-changing gift.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12049', 'streetAddress': 'Tempelhofer Feld'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.47461', 'longitude': '13.416562'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_980953d82b7c-S%C3%ADYoga_nel_parco_con_logo_1622206315452978_admin.jpg?alt=media'}

name: Tanzstudio Hellersdorf
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Tanzstudio Hellersdorf', 'description': 'In unseren Tanzstudios Steglitz & Hellersdorf hei√üen wir Sie herzlich zu unseren Gruppenstunden willkommen. Bei unseren Kursen in Hellersdorf gilt, dass sie speziell auf die Fitness-Bed√ºrfnisse bestimmter Altersgruppen entwickelt worden sind. Klassisches Ziel der Kurse ist die Verbesserung des Alltagsbefindens. Sie finden bei uns genau auf die jeweilige Altersgruppe speziell abgestimmtes Sport- und Fitnessprogramm, denn bei unseren Kursen steht die Funktionalit√§t des K√∂rpers im Vordergrund. Gerade bei Schmerzen oder Arthrosen kann Sport wahre Wunder bewirken. Deshalb haben alle unsere Kurse ein ausgewogenes Fitness-Konzept, Ihrem Alter angepasst. Sie trainieren Kraft, Kondition, Flexibilit√§t und Motorik. Bei uns beginnen, so einfach wie das ‚Äûeins, zwei, drei‚Äú: 1. Kurs nach Altersstruktur aussuchen 2. Jederzeit beginnen 3. Sich besser f√ºhlen Des Weiteren geben wir euch die M√∂glichkeiten, an unseren Tanzkursen im Tanzstudio-Steglitz teilzunehmen. ‚ÄûStep by step‚Äú ist unsere Philosophie. Ein speziell auf die heutige moderne Zeit entwickeltes Kurssystem behandelt immer nur einen Tanz. Im Vergleich zu anderen Unterrichtskonzepten bildet bei uns jede Unterrichtsstunde eine abgeschlossene Einheit. Der Lernerfolg ist intensiver und nachhaltiger als bei konventionellen Tanzkursen. Viele weitere Vorteile ergeben sich f√ºr unsere Kunden. Der Einstieg in einen Tanz ist zu jedem Termin m√∂glich und es entfallen lange Wartezeiten. Sie w√§hlen v√∂llig frei und individuell Ihre Wunschtermine und entsprechend dem Datum die Wunscht√§nze aus. Vers√§umte Termine k√∂nnen zielgerichtet nachgeholt werden. name: The Way Back Home - JOY Space
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'The Way Back Home - JOY Space', 'description': 'Yoga for The Way Back Home to ourSelves: A yoga and meditation practice rooted in nondual tantra philosophy, for revealing and (re)connecting to your true, essential nature, and for exploring ways of honouring your essence and its authentic expression. In nonduality, there is a recognition that everything in the universe, including ourselves, is Divine. And in tantra, this world we live in and perceive is not written off as an illusion, but rather embraced and worked with, also holding the potential to lead us back to the Divine. We will explore these philosophies more deeply through practice and our own direct experiences. Styles of practice include self-enquiry meditation, a meditative hatha, and a more somatic flow highlighting intuitive movement. If you‚Äôve felt a longing to connect more intimately to the expansive depth of your being through yoga, come practice with me :) Open to all levels.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10117', 'streetAddress': 'Albrechtstra√üe 19'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5224586', 'longitude': '13.3844949'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_3629x2041_3c7e38b8d51d-R1_05237_0006_1692002929871046_admin.jpg?generation=1692002930067239&alt=media'}

name: Triathlon Crew Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Triathlon Crew Berlin', 'description': 'Willkommen bei der Triathloncrew Berlin. Der Triathlonsport wird immer mehr zum Volkssport, bietet er doch viele M√∂glichkeiten sich sportlich zu fordern und weiterzuentwickeln. Aber aus welchen Disziplinen besteht der Triathlon? Im TRIATHLON steht als erste Disziplin das SCHWIMMEN an, gefolgt vom RADFAHREN und dem LAUFEN zum Schluss. Drei Disziplinen deren k√∂rperliche Anforderungen sehr verschieden ausfallen k√∂nnen. Entsprechend gibt es unter den Sportlern kaum jemanden der Experte in allen drei Disziplinen ist. Dieses Problem wollen wir von der Triathloncrew Berlin l√∂sen. Mitten in Berlin, Indoor und Outdoor, bieten wir ein sehr technikorientiertes Training aller Disziplinen an. Denn Schwimmen ist nicht gleich Schwimmen und Laufen nicht gleich Laufen. Die meisten unserer Kurse enthalten deshalb viele technische Komponente zur Steigerung der √ñkonomie und Effizienz, mit dem Ziel der Leistungsoptimierung. Dabei achten wir darauf immer auf dem neuesten Stand der wissenschaftlichen Lehrmeinung und Technik zu sein. Neuerungen flie√üen dabei sehr schnell in das Training mit ein. Besonders stolz sind wir darauf Berlins erstes und einziges SMART Rollentrainer-Radtraining anbieten zu k√∂nnen. Mithilfe Ihres eigenen Rades, und Ihrer eigenen individuellen Radeinstellung (auch nach Bikefitting), holen wir das Maximum aus Ihner Leistungsf√§higkeit heraus. Wir bieten folgende Kurse an: Schwimmen: ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik Open Water ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT Open Water ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining Open Water Radfahren mit dem eigenen Rad (Shimano Schaltung): ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining Technik ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining VO2max ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining LIT ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Bike Ausfahrt Laufen: ‚Ä¢tLauftechnik und -√∂konomietraining ‚Ä¢tHIT & Run ‚Ä¢tTriathloncrew Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Run Funktionelles Krafttraining: ‚Ä¢tTraining der Triathlonspezifischen Arbeitsmuskulatur ‚Ä¢tCoretraining ‚Ä¢tZugseiltraining Bei den Kursen handelt es sich um ausgesuchte Kurse, die jeweils nach Saison und Trainingsphase in das Training integriert werden k√∂nnen. Neben den Inhalten des Trainings ist eines der wichtigsten Erfolgsfaktoren zur Verbesserung der Leistungsf√§higkeit, die Kontinuit√§t des Trainings. Mit fachlicher Kompetenz, Spa√ü und Enthusiasmus freuen wir uns, Ihnen dabei unter die Arme greifen zu d√ºrfen. English: Welcome to the Triathlon Crew Berlin. Triathlon is becoming an ever more popular sport, since it offers many opportunities to challenge and further develop yourself and your sporting ability. But what disciplines does the triathlon consist of? TRIATHLON consists of SWIMMING, followed by BIKING and RUNNING at the end. Three disciplines whose physical requirements can be very different. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. We are particularly proud to be able to offer Berlin's first and only SMART bike training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. With professional competence, fun and enthusiasm, we look forward to helping you.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10435', 'streetAddress': 'Schwedter Str. 45'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5390676', 'longitude': '13.4053762'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1280x720_657E83FA-00E3-4EB4-87AF-68D2A5093259_1581590489873999_admin.jpeg?alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Upgrounding -  PHYNIXtanzt', 'description': 'My name is Vladimir Dziomba, I have been trained in teaching dance, the F.M. Alexander technique and the Pilates method, three different dimensions which I combine to develop new approaches and practises such as Lengthening Pilates and Upgrounding Developmental Movement, and to further my research about being a thinking body made of constant motion, and which is by essence, designed to be moving. I am looking forward to inviting you to experience how to rise from the floor by being suspended from the head, how to allow the triggering of the bio-mechanisms of motion of the body, how to move into space with ease and release, lightness and strength, span, and with much pleasure. Regardless of your professional field and of how much moving you do through the course of the week, a body made of movement and meant to be moving is what you are, and there is a way for you to make that pain-free, enjoyable and happy... : I welcome you for an Alexander technique lesson, a Lengthening Pilates session, an Upgrounding Developmental Movement class!', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10967', 'streetAddress': 'Hasenheide 54'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4895184', 'longitude': '13.4100195'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_6119x3442_36fa8fa7a5e9-UPG_first_image__1__1685714459852798_admin.png?generation=1685714459931488&alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Wave on Yoga - Ashtanga Yoga Shala Berlin', 'description': 'My name is Martina, as a yoga teacher, my goal is to offer a more complete, contemporary and functional practice. I include a vast range of movements techniques coming from pilates, functional and mobility training, martial arts, contemporary dance, somatic and Feldenkrais methods and more. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yannis Mitsos - Contemporary Dance Class', 'description': 'This class will be divided into three parts: warm up exercises and dance phrases (mostly floorwork based, core activating and muscle elongating), precision exercises and dynamic dance phrases. description: This class will be divided into three parts: warm up exercises and dance phrases (mostly floorwork based, core activating and muscle elongating), precision exercises and dynamic dance phrases. Der Ausgleich zwischen Bewegung & k√∂rperlicher Anstrengung und zwischen Ruhe & Entspannung hilft dabei, sich auf seine Atmung zu konzentrieren, den K√∂rper bewusst wahrzunehmen und seine Sinne nach innen zu richten. The asanas (yoga exercises) should strengthen the body and thereby also strengthen the mind. Hatha Yoga involves rather slow executions and stopping positions with breaks between the asanas. Der Ausgleich zwischen Bewegung & k√∂rperlicher Anstrengung und zwischen Ruhe & Entspannung hilft dabei, sich auf seine Atmung zu konzentrieren, den K√∂rper bewusst wahrzunehmen und seine Sinne nach innen zu richten. Ab und zu mixe ich auch Vinyasa Flow und du erlebst einen flie√üenden √úbergang einzelner Posen. Es wird in kleiner Gruppe praktiziert, so kann ich vielmehr auf einzelne Bed√ºrfnisse eingehen und niemand muss seine Yogamatte zwischen 50 weitere quetschen. Matten, Probs und Decken sind vorhanden, sowie Umkleiden und WC's. Hatha Yoga is well suited for beginners, but also experienced yoga practitioners can intensify and improve their yoga practice with Hatha Yoga. Translated from Sanskrit, Hatha means "powerful" or "conscious". Hatha Yoga activates the body and mind. You feel lighter, more balanced and therefore have more energy for the day. The asanas (yoga exercises) should strengthen the body and thereby also strengthen the mind. Hatha Yoga involves rather slow executions and stopping positions with breaks between the asanas. The balance between movement & physical exertion and between rest & relaxation helps to concentrate on your breathing, to consciously perceive the body and to direct your senses inwards. Now and then I do a mix of Hatha and Vinyasa Flow and you experience a smooth transition of individual poses. We practice in a small group, so I can rather respond to individual needs and nobody has to squeeze his yoga mat between 50 others. Mats, probs and blankets are available, as well a changing and bathroom.

name: Yogateacher Luka Joge - Shin Gi Tai Kai e.V.
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yogateacher Luka Joge - Shin Gi Tai Kai e.V.', 'description': 'Luka is a mover that hasn't stopped moving since he left his IT chair some years ago. He is a bubble of ideas; about life, Acroyoga, and massage/bodywork. Very rarely a day passes without some kind of movement practice or community / teaching events. Luka has been teaching the past years around the world with a yearly 3 month stay in Japan and also South America and Europe. With the organisation Japanero.pro he organises events ranging from yoga, Acroyoga, partner acrobatics, handstands, massage and running - usually always in beautiful nature places around Europe. Originally from Croatia he has now settled in Berlin and is starting with regular weekly classes in different movement areas. His certifications and experiences include - Acroyoga International Solar Immersion teacher - Partner Acrobatics teacher - Massage therapist (thai yoga massage, woutai = osteopathic dance massage) - outdoor climber - Long-term yoga practitioner - handstand enthusiast', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Reichenberger Stra√üe 124'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4955162', 'longitude': '13.4312863'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1800x1013_FRONTBILD_159368003166630_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
